1. DEFINITIONS
================================================================

"Licensed Material" means the Lean 4 source code, theorem statements,
proof scripts, build configuration files, documentation, and any other
files contained in this repository.

"You" or "Licensee" means the natural person or legal entity exercising
rights under this License.

"Academic Research" means use of the Licensed Material by a natural
person, including a student, postdoctoral researcher, faculty member, or
independent scholar, for any of the following purposes:

    (a) scholarly study and reading;
    (b) verification of proofs stated in the accompanying papers;
    (c) reproduction of results stated in the accompanying papers;
    (d) individual scientific investigation that does not produce
        institutional deliverables;
    (e) citation in the individual's own scholarly publications.

Academic Research includes use by an individual who is employed by or
affiliated with an academic institution, provided that the use is for
the individual's own scholarly understanding and is not part of any of
the activities described under Departmental Academic Use.

"Departmental Academic Use" means any use of the Licensed Material by,
on behalf of, or with the resources of an academic department,
university, research group, laboratory, research center, institute, or
other academic organization, including but not limited to:

    (a) integration into instructional materials for courses, seminars,
        or tutorials;
    (b) use in funded research projects, grant deliverables, or
        contracted research;
    (c) use in supervised student work that is part of an institutional
        program;
    (d) deployment as part of departmental, laboratory, or institutional
        infrastructure;
    (e) use in collaborative or joint research that produces
        deliverables attributed to one or more institutions;
    (f) any use that benefits an institution beyond an individual
        scholar's personal study.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Licensed Material in connection
with a commercial product, a commercial service, the internal business
operations of a for-profit entity, or any activity from which commercial
value is derived, whether directly or indirectly. Commercial Use
includes but is not limited to:

    (a) any use within for-profit entities, of any size;
    (b) use by government contractors or paid consultants in delivering
        contracted work;
    (c) use in software products, services, platforms, or APIs offered
        for sale, subscription, or any form of commercial distribution;
    (d) training, fine-tuning, evaluating, benchmarking, or otherwise
        developing any commercial machine-learning model, system, or
        service;
    (e) integration into a commercial product or service, whether
        shipped, hosted, embedded, or otherwise provided to third
        parties;
    (f) any use intended to produce commercial revenue, competitive
        advantage, or market positioning for any entity.

